        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2017-11-25 10:50:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nIt appears that ptlrpc_lprocfs_unregister_obd() is always following lprocfs_obd_cleanup(), so it would be easier to just move it to the end of ptlrpc_lprocfs_unregister_obd() so that it is always called in the right place, and simplifies the code a bit.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c722b632b5e50147a379542b4fec1aa8020623ca",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 229,
        "name": "Bruno Faccini",
        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2017-11-25 11:14:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAndreas, you mean to move ptlrpc_lprocfs_unregister_obd() to the end of lprocfs_obd_cleanup(), right ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e29cd0962102d717000b5de89a2e674144bab785",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2017-11-25 11:17:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSorry, I mean the opposite - move lprocfs_obd_cleanup() to the start of ptlrpc_lprocfs_unregister_obd().  We can't have code in obdclass accessing ptlrpc* functions due to module loading order issues.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
